      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKADO MANIA (1) comes off an average run last start when fifth at Sandown over 515m behind Uncle Stiltskin (30.20) in a Free For All. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and two minor placings from five starts. Should be very hard to beat this time. WHISKY BELLA (7) was prominent early from the tricky draw and did a fair job to be beaten 2.5 lengths into third (34.80) at The Meadows in a Grade 5 over 600m. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Will give a great sight again. MAUDIE ROSE (2) is mixing form and out of the placings last time but was a Grade 5 winner three starts ago and moves to Box 2 this time where she has performed well. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. HONEY STIRRER (8) is right in the mix.",
